<h2>Solar Incentives in Oakland</h2>
<p>Oakland residents have access to multiple solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, through 2032. This credit steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034 before expiring for residential installations. California's Self-Generation Incentive Program (SGIP) offers rebates for battery storage systems, providing up to \$1,000 per kWh of storage capacity for qualifying homeowners. PG&E customers benefit from net energy metering (NEM), which credits solar production at retail rates, though new customers are subject to NEM 3.0 rules that reduce export credits but still provide substantial savings when combined with battery storage.</p>

